G3:
Ἀβαδδών [N:N--T]
Abaddon — Ἀβαδδών (Heb. אֲבַדּוֹן, destruction; LXX, ἀπώλεια, only in Wisdom Lit., of the place of the ruined dead: Refs [Job 26:6, 28:22, 31:12, Psa 88:12, Pro 15:11]＊), indecl.; 
 in NT, Abaddon, the angel of the Abyss: Rev 9:11.†

G15:
ἀγαθοποιέω [G:V]
to do good — ἀγαθὀ-ποιέω, -ῶ (= cl. ἀγαθὸν ποιεῖν, εὐεργετεῖν), 
 [in LXX: Refs [Num 10:32, Jdg 17:13] A, Zep 1:12 (יטב hi.), Tob.12:13 B, Refs [1Ma.11:33, 2Ma.1:2] ＊ ;] 
to do good; 
__(a) univ.: Refs [1Pe 2:15, 20, 3:6, 17, 3Jo.11]; 
