G2106:
εὐδοκέω [G:V]
to delight — εὐ-δοκέω, -ῶ
 (on the derivation, see EL, § 28, 6) [in LXX chiefly for רָצָה, also for אָבָה, חָפֵץ, etc. ;] 
__1. with inf. (Polyb., al.), to be well pleased, to think it good, to give consent (so freq. in π. in legal docu­ments; Milligan, Th., 22 f.): Refs [Luk 12:32, Rom 15:26-27, 1Co 1:21, Gal 1:15, Col 1:19], R, mg. (ICC, in l, but see infr.), Refs [1Th 2:8 3:1]; μᾶλλον εὐ., 2Co 5:8; with accusative and inf. (Polyb., i, 8, 4), Col, l.with, R, txt. (Lft., in l). 
