 __(with) to suppose, judge, deem: 1Co 13:11; ὡς, 1Pe 5:12; οὕτως, 1Co 4:1; with accusative of thing(s), 2Co 3:5; id. before εἰς, 2Co 12:6; ὅτι, Rom 8:18; τοῦτο, ὅτι, Refs [Rom 2:3, 2Co 10:7]; with inf., 2Co 11:5; accusative and inf., Refs [Rom 3:28 14:14, Php 3:13]; with accusative of person(s) before ὡς, 2Co 10:2; 
 __(d) to purpose, decide: with inf. (Eur., Or., 555), 2Co 10:2 
