G4253:
πρό [G:Prep]
before — πρό 
 prep. with genitive, [in LXX chiefly for פָּנִים ;] 
before; 
 __(a) of place: Refs [Act 12:6, 14 14:13, Jas 5:9]; π. προσώπου (= Heb. פָּנִים, Deu 3:18, Mal 3:1, al.; Bl., § 40, 9), Refs [Mat 11:10, Mrk 1:2, Luk 1:76 7:27 9:52 10:1, Act 14:13]; 
 __(b) of time: Refs [Mat 8:29 24:38, Luk 11:38 21:12, Jhn 11:55 13:1 17:24, Act 5:36 21:38, 1Co 2:7 4:5, Eph 1:4, Col 1:17, 2Ti 1:9 4:21, Tit 1:2, Heb 11:5, 1Pe 1:20, Ju 25]; π. ἐτῶν δεκατεσσάρων, fourteen years ago, 2Co 12:2; π. προσώπου (see supr.), Act 13:24; with genitive of person(s), Refs [Mat 5:12, Jhn 5:7 10:8, Rom 16:7, Gal 1:17]; with genitive art. inf. (= πρίν; M, Pr., 100; Bl., § 69, 7), Refs [Mat 6:8 Luk 2:21 22:15, Jhn 1:49 13:19 17:5, Act 23:15, Gal 2:12 3:23]; as in late writers (resembling a Latin idiom but indepen­dent of it; B1., § 40, 5; M, Pr., 100 f.; of. Am 2Ma.15:36, and for other exx., Soph., Lex., see word), πρὸ ἓξ ἡμέρας τοῦ πάσχα, on the sixth day before the Passover, Jhn 12:1; 
 __(with) of preference: π. πάντων, Refs [Jas 5:12, 1Pe 4:8]; 
 __(d) in compos., 
