 __2. In NT, 
__(a) of the OT prophets: Refs [Mat 5:12, Mrk 6:15, Luk 4:27, Jhn 8:52, Rom 11:3, al.]; 
 __(b) of prophets in general: Refs [Mat 10:41 13:57 21:46, Mrk 6:4, Luk 13:33, al.]; 
 __(with) of John the Baptist: Refs [Mat 21:26, Mrk 6:15, Luk 1:76]; 
 __(d) of Christ: Refs [Mat 21:11, Jhn 6:14, Act 3:22, 23 7:37 (LXX)] ; 
 __(e) of Christian prophets in the apostolic age: Refs [Act 15:32, 1Co 12:28, Eph 2:20, al.]; 
 __(f) by meton., of the writings of prophets: Refs [Luk 24:27, Act 8:28, al.]; 
 __(g) of a poet: Tit 1:12 (on the use of the term in π. and Inscr., see Deiss., BS, 235f.; MM, xxii).

G4413:
πρῶτος [G:A]
first — B. Superl., πρῶτος, -η, -ον, 
 [in LXX chiefly for רִאשׁוֹן, also for אֶחַד, etc. ;] 
