 [in LXX chiefly for שָׁרַשׁ ;] 
a root: Refs [Mat 3:10, Luk 3:9]; ἐκ ῥιζῶν, Mrk 11:20; ῥ. ἔχειν, Refs [Mat 13:6, Mrk 4:6]; id. before ἐν ἑαυτῷ, fig., Refs [Mat 13:21, Mrk 4:17, Luk 8:13]. Metaph. (as in various senses in cl.), of cause, origin, source, etc.; 
